Happy New Year’s everyone! 2022 was a year of celebration for us. We worked ourselves to the bone, creating an album we are very proud of and this year we got to share it with you. As a bonus, we also got to collaborate with one of our favourite artists @eodmofficial on “Motherlode” and later in the year, perform it together with @fatherbadass & @vonstockula on stage. 

With live shows coming back, we had the opportunity to hit the road again and we got to share the stage with some incredible artists both in Canada and in the US of A: @officialshamansharvest @crobotband @saintasonia @adelitasway @thetrews @thewarningrockband & @threedaysgraceofficial . 

AND! Our duo became a trio. We welcomed in powerhouse bassist @brendan__mcmillan . 

Thank you to all of our fans and to our team for the epic ride. Rock And Roll Ain't Dead Until You’re Dead 🤟, see you in 2023.

-Jonny, Renee & B

location.city_name: Women's Rights Museum, Seneca Falls NY

social_posts.post_text: It's very cool to stand in such a significant place. I'm very grateful for these strong women who never gave up and who have paved the way. I have struggled with being taken seriously as a female drummer and as a woman in the music industry. In the beginning, I was laughed at in school and teased for playing drums. I've had people walk right past me and go to the guys for questions or to hand off cheques, knowing full well that I was their contact. I've been left to doubt myself out of fear that if I stand up to it I'll be called a Bitch or I'll be closing some door to another opportunity. I bet every woman can relate to some degree. But I'm still here (thanks to my warrior of a mother setting an example for me and to my supportive team and husband) and sometimes I am still fighting for equal respect as do all of the women in this industry. Here's to all the women who continue to fight for equality and to the men in our corner. 🤟❤️ Big love to you all.

Ottawa, ON 🇨🇦 Bronson Centre w/ Theory of A Deadman 05.04.2023

Last night around midnight in the pouring rain just south of Wawa, we hit a Moose. 

Our van was destroyed, but we all gratefully and unbelievably walked away unharmed. After an hour of help from the OPP and CAA we made it to Wawa, where we faced the inevitable... we were stuck and likely going to, for the first time in our bands history... miss a show. Then miraculously as insane as this sounds, at 1:30am an @ontarionorthland bus pulls up across the street and the driver (Chris Cavezza) after hearing our story agrees to take us to Thunder Bay AND with ALL of our gear. We still can't believe it... What a rollercoaster of emotions in that hour and a half. 

So we made it! We can't thank Chris enough for what he did or to everyone who answered the late night calls and texts to try and help us out. 

We say it and believe it but never lived it until now "Rock and Roll Ain't Dead Until You're Dead". 

See you tonight Thunder Bay. 🤟🤟🤟

Thank you Thunder Bay! 🔥 What a wild few days it's been. Big love to our friends @theorymusic and their crew for having us out with them, it was short, but it was epic. 

And a HUGE thanks to everyone for the outpouring of love after our accident. It means the world to us and we are so grateful to have such awesome fans. Much love. 

Up next UK & Germany! 🇬🇧🇩🇪 with @eodmofficial ✌️🤟🤘
